[White "Introduction"]
[Black "Introduction"]
[Result "*"]

{ Hello everyone!   Grandmaster Hikaru Nakamura here, with a new Chessable course on the greatest games that I have played in the King’s Indian. This is a very special opening to me, that many people have seen me play in many great games over the years.   For me though, the thing that’s really special about it is that there are a couple of games that I have played in this exciting opening and they are some of the best games that I have ever played. Specifically, the games that I played againstAlexander Beliavsky, andBoris Gelfand, which are games that I rank very highly overall. There are plenty of other games that I have won as well which we will be looking at in this course.   So make sure to check it out, and without further ado let’s start with one of the games that I won in this great opening. }
1. -- *

