{ Let's examine a few of White's other options:  A@@EndBracket@@@@StartFEN@@r4rk1/4ppbp/1q1p1np1/3P2B1/1np1PP2/2N2N2/PP2Q1PP/1R2K2R w K - 2 14@@EndFEN@@  14.Nd2  Nd3+  15.Kf1  Qd4  16.Nf3  Qa7-+  With tremendous attacking potential. Black is completely winning.   B.1@@EndBracket@@@@StartFEN@@r4rk1/4ppbp/1q1p1np1/3P2B1/1np1PP2/2N2N2/PP2Q1PP/1R2K2R w K - 2 14@@EndFEN@@  14.Qxc4  I suspect that I rejected Nb4 at the time because of this natural looking capture, but Black even has more than one move here. He shouldn't play  14...Qe3+?  15.Qe2  Nd3+  @@StartBracket@@or @@StartFEN@@r4rk1/4ppbp/3p1np1/3P2B1/1n2PP2/2N1qN2/PP2Q1PP/1R2K2R b K - 2 15@@EndFEN@@  15...Nc2+  16.Kf1+-  @@EndBracket@@@@StartFEN@@r4rk1/4ppbp/3p1np1/3P2B1/4PP2/2NnqN2/PP2Q1PP/1R2K2R w K - 3 16@@EndFEN@@  16.Kf1+-  but the following two moves are both fine.  B.2@@EndBracket@@@@StartFEN@@r4rk1/4ppbp/1q1p1np1/3P2B1/1nQ1PP2/2N2N2/PP4PP/1R2K2R b K - 0 14@@EndFEN@@  14...Nc2+  15.Kd2  Rfc8  16.Qe2  Ng4-+  Black is winning but this is a very hard move to find.   B.3@@EndBracket@@@@StartFEN@@r4rk1/4ppbp/1q1p1np1/3P2B1/1nQ1PP2/2N2N2/PP4PP/1R2K2R b K - 0 14@@EndFEN@@  14...Ng4!  15.Qe2  Rfc8  16.e5  @@StartBracket@@if @@StartFEN@@r1r3k1/4ppbp/1q1p2p1/3P2B1/1n2PPn1/2N2N2/PP2Q1PP/1R2K2R w K - 3 16@@EndFEN@@  16.h3  then  16...Ne3-+  @@EndBracket@@@@StartFEN@@r1r3k1/4ppbp/1q1p2p1/3PP1B1/1n3Pn1/2N2N2/PP2Q1PP/1R2K2R b K - 0 16@@EndFEN@@  16...Ne3-+  The knights are too powerful. }
