24. Qxg5
{ In the game, I opted for 24...Bg6. But there is a better move. Can you find it? }
24... Rf5 25. Qh4 Bf6 { A move that I completely missed during the game. } 26.
Nxf6 Ng6 27. Qxh5+
{ Or  27.Qe4  Qxf6-+  and Black's attack on the kingside is unstoppable. }
27... Rxh5 28. Nxh5 Qg5 29. cxd6 cxd6 30. Be2 Qd2 31. Kf1 Rf8
{ White has a rook and a bishop for the queen but is completely lost due to the lack of coordination of the pieces. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
