[SetUp "1"]

28. Bxa7
{ White got a little greedy here and took the pawn on a7. What is your punishment for this sin against chess? }
28... b5
{ White probably intended to answer  28...Qh1+  29.Kf2  e3  by sacrificing a piece on e3.  The pawn fork disrupts White's defence by forcing him to block his bishop's retreat. }
29. axb6
{ In the game White decided to sacrifice material with  29.Rb4  29...bxc4  30.Bxc4  Qh1+  @@StartBracket@@locking the king's emergency exit with 30...e3 would have been more precise@@EndBracket@@  31.Kf2  e3+  32.Bxe3  fxe3+  33.Kxe3  Nxf1+  34.Bxf1  Qg1+  . }
29... Bd4+ { The white queen is overloaded. } 30. Qxd4 { Or  30.Rf2  Qh1  . }
30... Nxe2# *

