[SetUp "1"]

17. h5 { White is about to open the h-file. How to react? } 17... Qxb2
{ The counter-attack is faster. White needs to tend to his rook before he can continue.  18.hxg6  looks dangerous but in reality, it does not threaten anything concrete, yet. }
18. Rb1 { 18.Rc1  c3  is similar. } 18... Qxa2 19. Rc1
{ The rook moves, before Black forces the knight away from defending it. }
19... c3 20. Nde4
{ 20.Rxc3  runs into  20...Qa4+  and now:  A@@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@r4rk1/pp1npp1p/4bnpQ/6NP/q7/2R2P2/3NP1P1/3K1B1R w - - 1 21@@EndFEN@@  21.Kc1  Rfc8  fuels the mating attack.   B@@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@r4rk1/pp1npp1p/4bnpQ/6NP/q7/2R2P2/3NP1P1/3K1B1R w - - 1 21@@EndFEN@@  21.Ke1  Qa1+  picks up the rook.   20.Nxe6  defending d2 while creating a mate threat himself is refuted by  20...Qxd2  21.Qxd2  cxd2  and White loses a piece. }
20... Bf5
{ The bishop finally retreats from the attack and fulfilling an offensive and defensive role at the same time. }
21. hxg6 Bxg6
{ Everything is under control and it is White who needs to worry about king safety. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
