[White "5. Exercises"]
[Black "Veselin Topalov vs. Hikaru Nakamura, Saint Louis 2016"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r2q1rk1/5pb1/3pb1p1/n1p1n2p/Np2P3/1P1B1P2/P2QNBPP/2RR2K1 w - - 0 20"]
[SetUp "1"]

20. Nf4
{ White has a firm grip on the light squares and would probably like to tighten it by exchanging off Black's light-squared bishop on e6. How does Black make progress? }
20... Bxb3
{ Of course, Black does not retreat the bishop. He turns it into a battering ram to break down the blockade. }
21. axb3 Nxb3 22. Qc2 Nxc1 23. Rxc1 Bh6
{ Black's position has improved a lot. The queenside pawns are liberated and White's pieces are awkwardly placed. It is already difficult to save all the loose pieces. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
