[White "5. Exercises"]
[Black "Conrad Holt vs. Hikaru Nakamura, Saint Louis 2015"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r5k1/ppp2rb1/3pB3/3Pp3/2P1q2N/3b2P1/PPnQ1P2/R1B3KR w - - 0 25"]
[SetUp "1"]

25. Nf5
{ The knight looks really active on f5 but it misses the point. Remind White who is the one attacking here. }
25... Ne1 26. Ne7+
{ Since White cannot parry both threats, he starts a desperate attempt to drum up counterplay. }
26... Kf8 27. Ng6+ Ke8
{ Simply stepping out of the way and keeping the threats alive is the road to victory.   27...Qxg6  28.Qxe1  would be better for White. }
*

