[SetUp "1"]

20. Qa5
{ White doesn't immediately tend to the tension in the centre and decides to attack the knight first. Black is winning now. }
20... Qe8
{ Simply stepping out of the way and protecting the knight does the job. Now captures on d6 would open the e-file with a check and there is still a double threat of ...g6-g5 and dxe5 looming. }
21. O-O
{ 21.Ne4  @@StartBracket@@opening an escape route for the bishop@@EndBracket@@  21...dxe5  not only loses material but opens up the position. There is no shelter for the white king. }
21... g5 { Collecting the trapped bishop. } *

