30. d6
{ White decided to drive the black queen to greener pastures. Thank him for his courtesy and accept the invitation. }
30... Qh4
{ Black chose a different winning method:  30...Qf6  31.Rh3  Rag8  32.Bf3  Nd4  33.Nxd4  Bxh3  34.Nb3  e4  . }
31. Rh3
{ After  31.h3  Ng3+  32.Kh2  Ne4  33.Qe1  the best option is to slowly improve the position with moves like Nf2,  Rag8,  e5-e4. Have faith in Black's attack, Stockfish already gives mate in 17 on higher depths.  However, there is also an immediate way to cash in:  33...Qg3+!  34.Rxg3  fxg3+  35.Kh1  Nf2+  36.Qxf2  gxf2  and Black has a big advantage - just not as big as it could be with patient preparation. }
31... Qxh3 32. gxh3 Bc6+
{ 33.Rg2  Rxg2  followed by a discovered check is lethal.   White's only way to prevent mate is to sacrifice the queen back with  33.Qd5  , but that would leave him an exchange down in a hopeless endgame. }
