27. Rd1
{ A@@EndBracket@@  27.fxe4  Rf1+!  28.Kg2  Be3!  threatens  29.--  Rg1  30.Kh3  Qf1  31.Bxf1  Bxg4  . However, after @@StartFEN@@r4qk1/2Rb4/p2p2n1/1p1Pp3/4P1Pp/N2Nb3/PPQ1B1KP/2R1Br2 w - - 3 29@@EndFEN@@  29.Bxf1  h3+  30.Kg3  Qxf1  the threat of  31.--  Bf4  31.Nxf4  exf4  ends the game.   B@@EndBracket@@  27.Rxd7  Rxf3!  28.Bxf3  Qxf3+  29.Qg2  Qxd3  threatens ...h3 followed by ...Qf3. Therefore  30.Rd1  , trying to distract the queen, but  Bd2!!  short-circuits the security system @@StartBracket@@@@StartFEN@@r5k1/3R4/p2p2nb/1p1Pp3/4n1Pp/N2q4/PP4QP/3RB2K b - - 1 30@@EndFEN@@  30...Qxd1?  31.Qxe4  would allow counterplay@@EndBracket@@:   B1@@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@r5k1/3R4/p2p2n1/1p1Pp3/4n1Pp/N2q4/PP1b2QP/3RB2K w - - 2 31@@EndFEN@@  31.Rxd2  Nxd2  32.Bxd2  @@StartBracket@@the white queen needs to guard against ...Qf1 mate@@EndBracket@@  32...h3  33.Qf2  Rf8  is curtains.   B2@@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@r5k1/3R4/p2p2n1/1p1Pp3/4n1Pp/N2q4/PP1b2QP/3RB2K w - - 2 31@@EndFEN@@  31.Bxd2  Nf4  and White is getting mated or suffers a hefty loss of material in all lines. For example  32.Be1  Nf2  33.Qxf2  Qe4  34.Kg1  Nh3  35.Kf1  Nxf2  36.Bxf2  Qxg4  37.Ke1  Qxd7  .   C@@EndBracket@@  27.Nc5  dxc5  28.Qxe4  Bxc1  29.Qxg6  Rg7  leaves Black material up with the initiative.   D@@EndBracket@@  27.Nf2  Nxf2+  28.Bxf2  Bxc1  29.Qxg6+  Rg7  is similar. }
