15. fxg4
{ 15.Bg2  was played in the game and Black won after a long endgame:  15...a6  16.Nbc3  Bc8  17.Bh6  Nh5  18.O-O-O  Nd7  19.Bxg7  Kxg7  20.Ng3  Ndf6  21.Nxh5+  Nxh5  22.f4  Qf6  23.Rdf1  Qd4  24.Qe2  Ng3  25.Qf3  Nxh1  26.Rxh1  h5  27.f5  Bxf5  28.exf5  Qe3+  29.Qxe3  Rxe3  30.Kd2  Rg3  31.Be4  Re8  32.Rf1  Rxc3  33.fxg6  fxg6  34.Bxg6  Kxg6  35.Kxc3  h4  36.Kb3  h3  37.Ka4  Rb8  38.b3  Rh8  39.Ka5  h2  40.Rh1  Kf5  41.Kxa6  Ke5  42.a4  Kxd5  43.Kb7  Rh3  44.a5  Rxb3+  45.Kc7  Rb2  46.a6  Ra2  47.Kb7  c4  48.a7  Rb2+  49.Kc7  Ra2  50.Kb7  c3  51.Rxh2  Rxh2  52.a8=Q  c2  53.Kb6+  Kd4  54.Qa1+  Kd3  55.Qf1+  Re2  56.Kb5  Kd2  57.Qf4+  Kd1  58.Qf1+  Kd2  59.Qf4+  Re3  60.Qf2+  Kd3  61.Qf1+  Kc3  62.Ka4  Kd2  63.Qf2+  Kd3  64.Qf5+  Kd2  65.Qf1  Rd3  66.Qf2+  Kc3  67.Qf1  Rd4+  68.Ka3  Rd1  69.Qf3+  Rd3  and Hikaru won on time. }
15... Nxe4 16. Qc1
{ The most stubborn defense. White is trying to keep the bishop on e3 protected without any potential deflections in the air.  After  16.Qd3  Qa5+  is not the only winning move but a pretty forcing one:  17.Nbc3  c4  18.Qxc4  Nxc3  19.bxc3  Rxe3-+  . }
16... Nd7
{ The strongest move. Black is just bringing another piece in the attack.   16...Qa5+  17.Nbc3  Nd7  is similar. }
17. Bg2 Rb8
{ Even stronger than ...Qa5+. Now White has also problems with his pawn on b2 and Black's Queen has also options of the e-file. }
18. Nbc3 Nxc3 19. bxc3 Qe7 { Pinning the Bishop on e3. } 20. Rh3 Ne5
{ And it is impossible to stop all the threats. } 21. Qc2 Rb2
{ This would be a nice final touch. } 22. Qxb2 Nd3+ *

