{ Threatens Qf3+. White doesn't have too many options.   If instead  21...Ne1  then  22.Qe2  and the game still continues. }
22. Nxf5
{ 22.Qe2  Nxe2  23.Nxf5  Nxf2  is the cute little difference to 21...Ne1. }
22... Nxc2
{ White can exchange pieces on g7, but Black's main threats are ... Nxa1 or...Nxf2 followed by ...Nxd1. White cannot handle both threats. }
23. Nxg7 Kxg7 24. Bb2 { Or  24.Ra2  Nxf2+  25.Kg1  Nxd1  . } 24... Nxa1
{ There is nothing wrong with this greedy capture. Black is winning. } *

